-- Aviva says CFO Regan to leave 
-- By Brenda Goh
-- Thu Jan 23, 2014 02:14AM EST
-- None



LONDON, Jan 23 (Reuters) - Aviva <AV.L> said on Thursday its chief financial officer (CFO) Pat Regan would be stepping down in June to join QBE <QBE.AX> as the Australian insurer's CFO.

Regan joined Aviva in February 2010 as CFO. The company said formal arrangements for his replacement were in progress.  "Pat has been a tremendous support in assisting me with Aviva's financial transformation. I am supportive of his decision, and he leaves with my best wishes and those of Aviva's board," Aviva's Chief Executive Mark Wilson said.